 work yields a new set of conceptual questions and practical issues and provides new energy to the dialogue on political and cultural modernity. In cross-cultural context, Zhang finds the answers to the question "What is enlightenment?" are multiple, pluralistic, dynamic, and self-renewing.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aEnlightenmentzChina. 0aEnlightenmentzEurope. 0aPhilosophy, Comparative. 4aAsian Studies : Chinese Religion and Philosophy. 4aAsian Studies : Chinese Studies. 4aPhilosophy : Comparative Philosophy. 4aPhilosophy : Hermeneutics. 7aPHILOSOPHY / History & Surveys / Modern.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013z978311148737340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438431079423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438431079/original  a978-3-11-148737-3  SUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles